 Worth</a>, September 8, 2012.  \r\n   ]]></description>\r\n         <pubDate>Sat, 8 Sep 2012 12:23:11 -0400</pubDate>\r\n         <guid>http://www.downes.ca/link/3838</guid>\r\n                <category domain=\"http://www.downes.ca/topic/\">none</category>\n\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n\r\n   <title>Learning Analytics and the Hands of Evil</title>\r\n   <link>http://www.downes.ca/cgi-bin/edurss02.cgi?rd=3836</link>\r\n   <description><![CDATA[Who&#8217;s Afraid of the Power (cc) Flickr Photo by Emersunn I just learned about &#8220;learning analytics&#8221; from Audry Waters, a blogger/journalist whom I am reading with increasing regularity. Reporting on the recent Learning Analytics and Knowledge conference in Vancouver, Waters shared a phrase that was used often at the conference, &#8220;data exhaust.&#8221; The first time [...] <a  href=\"http://www.downes.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?feed=14\" class=\"stealth\">2Â¢ Worth</a>, September 8, 2012.  \r\n   ]]></description>\r\n         <pubDate>Sat, 8 Sep 2012 12:23:10 -0400</pubDate>\r\n         <guid>http://www.downes.ca/link/3836</guid>\r\n                <category domain=\"http://www.downes.ca/topic/14\">Flickr</category>\n      <category domain=\"http://www.downes.ca/topic/153\">Web Logs</category>\n\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n\r\n   <title>David\'s \"Great Moments in EdTech History\"</title>\r\n   <link>http://www.downes.ca/cgi-bin/edurss02.cgi?rd=3835</link>\r\n   <description><![CDATA[A few weeks ago, Dean Shareski wrote a blog post (Great Moments in EdTech History), where he said, I wanted to look back at my personal journey into educational technology and share a few instances of \"aha moments\" that I think many can relate to. I so agreed with the items on his list â€“ [...] <a  href=\"http://www.downes.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?feed=14\" class=\"stealth\">2Â¢ Worth</a>, September 8, 2012.  \r\n   ]]></description>\r\n         <pubDate>Sat, 8 Sep 2012 12:23:09 -0400</pubDate>\r\n         <guid>http://www.downes.ca/link/3835</