books&#8221; [...] <a  href=\"http://www.downes.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?feed=14\" class=\"stealth\">2Â¢ Worth</a>, September 8, 2012.  \r\n   ]]></description>\r\n         <pubDate>Sat, 8 Sep 2012 12:23:12 -0400</pubDate>\r\n         <guid>http://www.downes.ca/link/3840</guid>\r\n                <category domain=\"http://www.downes.ca/topic/173\">Books</category>\n      <category domain=\"http://www.downes.ca/topic/153\">Web Logs</category>\n\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n\r\n   <title>The Nextbook Must Be...</title>\r\n   <link>http://www.downes.ca/cgi-bin/edurss02.cgi?rd=3837</link>\r\n   <description><![CDATA[&#160; (cc) janthepea For a science fiction look at textbooks, read about The Young Lady&#8217;s Illustrated Primer in The Diamond Age and Ender&#8217;s desk in Ender&#8217;s Game. If you have other suggestions, please comment. &#160; A couple of weeks ago, my friend, Tom Whitby, wrote a blog article, We Don&#8217;t Need No Stink&#8217;n Textbooks. I [...] <a  href=\"http://www.downes.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?feed=14\" class=\"stealth\">2Â¢ Worth</a>, September 8, 2012.  \r\n   ]]></description>\r\n         <pubDate>Sat, 8 Sep 2012 12:23:11 -0400</pubDate>\r\n         <guid>http://www.downes.ca/link/3837</guid>\r\n                <category domain=\"http://www.downes.ca/topic/173\">Books</category>\n      <category domain=\"http://www.downes.ca/topic/153\">Web Logs</category>\n\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n\r\n   <title>About Creativity from Jonah Lehrer</title>\r\n   <link>http://www.downes.ca/cgi-bin/edurss02.cgi?rd=3838</link>\r\n   <description><![CDATA[Jonah Lehrer We hurried back from Cullowhee Thursday so that I could see Jonah Lehrer talk about his new book, Imagine, at the Quail Ridge Bookstore in Raleigh. Â We&#8217;d been in Cullowhee for events leading up to the installation of Western Carolina University&#8217;s new chancellor, Dr. David Belcher. Â Brenda and I both graduated from WCU [...] <a  href=\"http://www.downes.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?feed=14\" class=\"stealth\">2Â¢ Worth</a>, September 8, 2012.  \r\n   ]]></description>\r\n         <pubDate>Sat, 8 Sep 2012 12:23:11 -0400</pubDate>\r\n         <guid>http://www.downes.ca/link/3838</guid>\r\n                <category domain=\"http://www.downes.ca/topic/\">none</category>\n\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n\r\n   <title>Learning Analytics and the Hands of Evil</title>\r\n   <link>http://www.downes.ca/cgi-bin/edurss02.cgi?rd=3836</link>\r\n   <description><![CDATA[Who&#8217;s Afraid of the Power (cc) Flickr Photo by Emersunn I just learned about &#8220;learning analytics&#8221; from Audry Waters, a blogger/journalist whom I am reading with increasing regularity. Reporting on the recent Learning Analytics and Knowledge conference in Vancouver, Waters shared a phrase that was used often at the conference, &#8220;data exhaust.&#8221; The first time [...] <a  href=\"http://www.downes.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?feed=14\" class=\"stealth\">2Â¢ Worth</a>, September 8, 2012.  \r\n   ]]></description>\r\n         <pubDate>Sat, 8 Sep 2012 12:23:10 -0400</pubDate>\r\n         <guid>http://www.downes.ca/link/3836</guid>\r\n                <category domain=\"http://www.downes.ca/topic/14\">Flickr</category>\n      <category domain=\"http://www.downes.ca/topic/153\">Web Logs</category>\n\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n\r\n   <title>David\'s \"Great Moments in EdTech History\"</title>\r\n   <link>http://www.downes.ca/cgi-bin/edurss02.cgi?rd=3835</link>\r\n   <description><![CDATA[A few weeks ago, Dean Shareski wrote a blog post (Great Moments in EdTech History), where he said, I wanted to look back at my personal journey into educational technology and share a few instances of \"aha moments\" that I think many can relate to. I so agreed with the items on his list â€“ [...] <a  href=\"http://www.downes.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?feed=14\" class=\"stealth\">2Â¢ Worth</a>, September 8, 2012.  \r\n   ]]></description>\r\n         <pubDate>Sat, 8 Sep 2012 12:23:09 -0400</pubDate>\r\n         <guid>http://www.downes.ca/link/3835</guid>\r\n                <category domain=\"http://www.downes.ca/topic/153\">Web Logs</category>\n\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n\r\n   <title>Who Wouldn\'t Want Students to Learn Critical Thinking Skills?</title>\r\n   <link>http://www.downes.ca/cgi-bin/edurss02.cgi?rd=3833</link>\r\n   <description><![CDATA[I mentioned this on some social networks the other day, but thought I&#8217;d post it here as well. I recently got a call from an automated polling service, which promised me a trip for two to the Bahamas if I would complete the short political survey. I pressed the number for &#8220;yes,&#8221; more out of [...] <a  href=\"http://www.downes.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?feed=14\" class=\"stealth\">2Â¢ Worth</a>, September 8, 2012.  \r\n   ]]></description>\r\n         <pubDate>Sat, 8 Sep 2012 12:23:08 -0400</pubDate>\r\n         <guid>http://www.downes.ca/link/3833</guid>\r\n                <category domain=\"http://www.downes.ca/topic/77\">Networks</category>\n\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n\r\n   <title>Becoming Future-Ready</title>\r\n   <link>http://www.downes.ca/cgi-bin/edurss02.cgi?rd=3834</link>\r\n   <description><![CDATA[&#8220;Future-Ready Students for the 21st Century&#8221; It&#8217;s the title of the goals document for the North Carolina State Board of Education and it begins with, &#8220;..every public school student will graduate from high school, globally competitive for work and postsecondary education and prepared for life in the 21st Century.&#8221; Â I&#8217;d love to ask that appointed [...] <a  href=\"http://www.downes.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?feed=14\" class=\"stealth\">2Â¢ Worth</a>, September 8, 2012.  \r\n   ]]></description>\r\n         <pubDate>Sat, 8 Sep 2012 12:23:08 -0400</pubDate>\r\n         <guid>http://www.downes.ca/link/3834</guid>\r\n                <category domain=\"http://www.downes.ca/topic/119\">Schools</category>\n\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n\r\n   <title>Education Blogger Survey</title>\r\n   <link>http://www.downes.ca/cgi-bin/edurss02.cgi?rd=3830</link>\r\n   <description><![CDATA[I learned, via Hack Education, about a survey from the Institute of Educational Technology (The Open University). Announced by Alice Bell in her blog, the study is based on work they did last year exploring brain bloggers (early data). Go here to get and complete the survey, and do it now â€“ because today&#8217;s the [...] <a  href=\"http://www.downes.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?feed=14\" class=\"stealth\">2Â¢ Worth</a>, September 8, 2012.  \r\n   ]]></description>\r\n         <pubDate>Sat, 8 Sep 2012 12:23:07 -0400</pubDate>\r\n         <guid>http://www.downes.ca/link/3830</guid>\r\n                <category domain=\"http://www.downes.ca/topic/153\">Web Logs</category>\n      <category domain=\"http://www.downes.ca/topic/90\">Google</category>\n      <category domain=\"http://www.downes.ca/topic/215\">Blogger</category>\n\r\n</item>\r\n<item>\r\n\r\n   <title>Should the Tools Drive the Learning?</title>\r\n   <link>http://www.downes.ca/cgi-bin/edurss02.cgi?rd=3831</link>\r\n   <description><![CDATA[(cc) photo by MrPessimist I spent Wednesday morning at the &#8220;Every Teacher Every Learner&#8221; conference in College Park Georgia. The event was organized by Woodward Academy and mostly for private school teachers from the area. I talked about contemporary literacy (learning-literacy) and about new pedagogies. In reviewing and commenting on the backchannel transcript this morning, [...] <a  href=\"http://www.downes.ca/cgi-bin/page.cgi?feed=14\" class=\"stealth\">2Â¢ Worth</a>, September 8, 2012.  \r\n   ]]></description>\r\n         <pubDate>Sat, 8 Sep 2012 12:23:07 -0400</pubDate>\r\n         <guid>http://www.downes.ca/link/3831</guid>\r\n                <category domain=\"http://www.downes.ca/topic/119\">Schools</category>\n      <category domain=\"http://www.downes.ca/topic/65\">Private Schools</category>\n      <category domain=\"http://www.downes.ca/topic/172\">Online Learning</category>\n\r\n</item>\r\n\r\n\r\n   </channel>\r